        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Eric S. Raymond'); ?>
        <p><strong>Eric Steven Raymond</strong> (born 4 December 1957), often referred to as <strong>ESR</strong>, is an American computer programmer, author and open source software advocate.</p>
        <p>After the 1997 publication of <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('The Cathedral and the Bazzaar', 'B'); ?>, Raymond was for a number of years frequently quoted as an unofficial spokesman for the open source movement.</p>
        <p>He is also known for his work on the popular Roguelike game <strong>Nethack</strong> for which he wrote the Guidebook, in addition to being a member of the "Dev-Team".</p>
        <p>More recently, he is recognized in certain circles for his 1990 edit and later updates of the <em>Jargon File</em>, currently in print as <strong>The New Hacker's Dictionary</strong>.</p>
